<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 8:54AM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Macon,
northeastern Marion, Schley and southwestern Taylor Counties through
1000 AM EDT...
At 853 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Murrays Crossroads, or
7 miles northwest of Ellaville. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Buena Vista, Ellaville, Putnam, Brantley, Murrays Crossroads, La
Crosse, Charing, Oakland, Mauk, Tazewell, Doyle, Bumphead, Walls
Crossing and Fountainville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
